output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of Physics and astronomy, one year after graduation, Professional, scientific and technical activities was the most common industry for White ethnicity graduates, Education, Financial and insurance activities, Human health and social work activities and Information and communication were the most common industries for Black / African / Caribbean / Black British ethnicity graduates, Information and communication was the most common industry for Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates, and Information and communication and Professional, scientific and technical activities were the most common industries for Mixed / Multiple ethnic groups, Other ethnic group and Unknown ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Information and communication where Other ethnic group ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and White ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion. The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Administrative and support service activities where Mixed / Multiple ethnic groups ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (23,000) and Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (14,200). The group with the highest earnings was Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates who worked in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of 39,100).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of Physics and astronomy by ethnicity, one year after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from HE providers, 2021/22 tax year.
